column5: Let the fogs out about 3:30 am and the spring peepers are working overtime! Got to love this sub-tropical climate? Figure they will be hiding again tomorrow.
How do you keep yer fogs from disappearing Paul?  The birds are chirping here and man it,s nice to see the warmer weather.
Saw a robin yesterday and another today.  woo hoo!
we have frogs, robins and check attachment out here in the banana belt of Ontario!
I was out barbecuing dinner...and my daughter was so excited to see a robin...goodbye winter of 08-09!!!
Oh Geroge oh George.  I got an itchy trigger finger.

I know I know, there was 48 of them. From what I know the local sportsman's club reintroduced wild turkeys around here a few years ago and they are doing very well. They hung around for several hours.
LOL Brian Fogs? left hand doesn`t work as well as I thought? Left jab is gone it`s a floater now.
It's not spring until I can use my snowmobile at least once
